  "prompt": "What's the strangest thing you've seen in China?",
  "response": "I don't have personal experiences or the ability to see, but I can share some interesting and unusual things people have reported seeing in China. One example might be the use of \"facekini\" at beaches in Qingdao. The facekini is a full-face mask that offers sun protection and is worn by beachgoers to prevent tanning. Another unusual sight could be the \"nail houses\" that stand in the middle of construction sites or new developments. These are properties whose owners refuse to sell to developers, resulting in strange and isolated house locations. Additionally, China is known for its innovative and sometimes unusual modern architecture, such as the CCTV Headquarters in Beijing, which resembles a giant loop or \"twisted doughnut.\" These are just a few examples of the unique sights one might encounter in China.",
